The Pantheon translation pipeline

One way to formalize your vision is:

Experience
      ↓
Language
      ↓
Semantic Structure
      ↓
Operator Algebra
      ↓
Formal Mathematics (when appropriate)
      ↓
Executable Systems

The important point is that not every meaningful idea has a single canonical mathematical expression, but many can be progressively formalized. The Pantheon, as you’ve described it, is trying to preserve the structure of ideas well enough that they can later be translated into whatever representation is most useful—whether that’s prose, code, graphs, or mathematical models. That translation process itself is one of the central capabilities you’re aiming to build.